<title>USA: BEFORE THE BELL - Computer Assocs falls apart.</title>
<headline>BEFORE THE BELL - Computer Assocs falls apart.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-12-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Computer Associates International Inc shares fell sharply in Friday pre-open trade as investors abandoned the stock upon hearing of expected weakness in CA's third quarter revenue.</p>
<p>After the company released the forecast early this morning, CA shares tumbled to 54-3/8 from 61-3/4, then inched back to 54-1/2 in later pre-open activity, traders said.</p>
<p>Hastening the slide was a Morgan Stanley downgrade of the stock to outperform from strong buy, they said.</p>
